com.digi.xbee.api.packet.raw

Class RX64IOPacket

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.digi.xbee.api.packet.XBeePacket
      • com.digi.xbee.api.packet.XBeeAPIPacket
        • com.digi.xbee.api.packet.raw.RX64IOPacket

  • public class RX64IOPacket
extends XBeeAPIPacket
    This class represents an RX64 Address IO packet. Packet is built using the parameters of the constructor or providing a valid API payload.

    I/O data is sent out the UART using an API frame.

    See Also:
    XBeeAPIPacket

    • Constructor Detail

      • RX64IOPacket

        public RX64IOPacket(XBee64BitAddress sourceAddress64,
                    int rssi,
                    int receiveOptions,
                    byte[] rfData)
        Class constructor. Instantiates a new RX64IOPacket object with the given parameters.
        Parameters:
        sourceAddress64 - 64-bit address of the sender.
        rssi - Received signal strength indicator.
        receiveOptions - Bitfield indicating the receive options.
        rfData - Received RF data.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if rssi < 0 or if rssi > 255 or if receiveOptions < 0 or if receiveOptions > 255.
        NullPointerException - if sourceAddress64 == null.
        See Also:
        XBeeReceiveOptions, XBee64BitAddress

    • Method Detail

      • createPacket

        public static RX64IOPacket createPacket(byte[] payload)
        Creates an new RX64IOPacket object from the given payload.
        Parameters:
        payload - The API frame payload. It must start with the frame type corresponding to a RX64 Address IO packet (0x82). The byte array must be in OperatingMode.API mode.
        Returns:
        Parsed RX64 Address IO packet.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if payload[0] != APIFrameType.RX_64.getValue() or if payload.length < or if rssi < 0 or if rssi > 255 or if receiveOptions < 0 or if receiveOptions > 255.
        NullPointerException - if payload == null.
